  <div class="container container--narrow">

    <header class="page-header" style="text-align: center;">
      <span class="card__eyebrow">Book</span>
      <h1 class="page-title" style="view-transition-name: page-title;">Welcome to Tomorrow</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle" style="margin-inline: auto;">A beginner's guide to technology</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-12);">

      <blockquote>
        This book will guide you on your first steps into careers in technology.
        My mission is to prepare you for your future by highlighting both the
        opportunity and risks in technology.
      </blockquote>

      <h2>What This Book Is About</h2>

      <p>
        <em>Welcome to Tomorrow</em> is a non-fiction technology educational work that guides readers
        in plain language on a tour of technology's tools and impacts throughout society.
        Written for anyone who wants to understand technology but doesn't know where to start.
      </p>

      <p>
        Whether you're a student exploring career paths, a professional pivoting into tech,
        or simply curious about how the digital world works — this book meets you where you are
        and walks you through the landscape in clear, approachable language.
      </p>

      <h2>Why I Wrote It</h2>

      <p>
        Technology is the most powerful force shaping our world, but the conversation around it
        often excludes the people who need to understand it most. I wrote <em>Welcome to Tomorrow</em>
        because I believe everyone deserves a seat at the table — not just those who already speak the language.
      </p>

      <p>
        This is the same belief that drives <a href="/cocovox/">Cocovox</a>: that learning tools
        should be accessible to everyone, that understanding shouldn't be locked behind jargon,
        and that tomorrow belongs to everyone willing to show up and learn.
      </p>

      <h2>Where to Find It</h2>

      <p>
        The full manuscript is available. Published June 6, 2017 — and the themes are more relevant today than ever.
      </p>

      <div style="margin-block-start: var(--space-8); display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); flex-wrap: wrap;">
